{
  "texts": [
    "Better ways of fine-tuning or prompting the model are only starting to be explored (Dettmers et al. 2023; Yao et al. 2023).",
    "5 One could argue that we would expect LLM performance to level off around human intelligence levels because LLMs are trained on human text.",
    "However, it also seems that LLMs have various advantages to humans, e.g.",
    "faster processing and bigger (working) memory capacity.",
    "Thus, we would expect that-if the training data are the only constraint on capability improvements in LLMs due to scaling-LLM nevertheless learn to do superhuman reasoning with human training data."
  ]
}